get.description: Retrieve results based on search query

parameters.name: language
parameters.description: Language code

parameters.name: searchText
parameters.description: The text that needs to be used for the search

parameters.name: searchCount
parameters.description: Format - int32. The maximum amount of results that will be returned. A value greater than 100 returns bad request error.

parameters.name: facetCount
parameters.description: Format - int32. The maximum amount of items per facet that will be retuned. Use 0 to disable the facets to be retuned.

parameters.name: categoryFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on categories. Repeat this parameter for each category value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: categoryFilter[]=Cars or categoryFilter[]=Cars&categoryFilter[]=Light commercial vehicles (< 7.5t)

parameters.name: makeFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on makes. Repeat this parameter for each make value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: makeFilter[]=Mazda (EU) or makeFilter[]=Mazda (EU)&makeFilter[]=Mercedes-Benz (EU)

parameters.name: modelFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on models. Repeat this parameter for each model value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: modelFilter[]=CX-5 or modelFilter[]=CX-5&modelFilter[]=E-Class

parameters.name: cilinderCapacityFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on cilinder capacities. Repeat this parameter for each cilinder capacity value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: cilinderCapacityFilter[]=2.0 or cilinderCapacityFilter[]=2.0&cilinderCapacityFilter[]=3.0

parameters.name: driveTypeFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on drive types. Repeat this parameter for each drive type value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: driveTypeFilter[]=f.w.d. or driveTypeFilter[]=f.w.d.&driveTypeFilter[]=r.w.d.

parameters.name: fuelFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on fuels. Repeat this parameter for each fuel value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: fuelFilter[]=Petrol or fuelFilter[]=Petrol&fuelFilter[]=Diesel

parameters.name: powerKwFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on power kW. Repeat this parameter for each power kW value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: powerKwFilter[]=150 or powerKwFilter[]=150&powerKwFilter[]=160

parameters.name: powerHpFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on power HP. Repeat this parameter for each power HP value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples: powerHpFilter[]=110 or powerHpFilter[]=110&powerHpFilter[]=120

parameters.name: yearFilter[]
parameters.description: Filter value to apply on years. Repeat this parameter for each year value to include in the filter. The filter value must match exactly the value from the returned facet. Examples:  yearFilter[]=2021 or yearFilter[]=2021&yearFilter[]=2022
